  "texts": [
    "https://garak.ai [27,28].It is well-established that LLMs may mediate harms [29].",
    "These harms and the risk of them manifesting have been structured in several taxonomies [30,31].",
    "The language model risk cards framework translates this work into a methodology for performing due diligence on technology that uses LLMs, including an enumeration of concrete, demonstrable harms and how to evaluate them [32].",
    "An increasing amount of work also focuses on how professionals perceive threats from generative AI [33].",
    "However, less is known about which harms or risks are accessible through attacking LLMs, or how attackers perceive and evaluate these harms.The NIST Adversarial Machine Learning Taxonomy [34] classifies attacks according to their learning method and stage of the learning process when the attack is mounted, the attacker's goals and objectives, the attacker's capabilities, and the attacker's knowledge of the learning process."
